The Minister of Defence, Mansur Dan-Ali, has directed the Chief of Army Staff (COAS) Lieutenant General Tukur Buratai to remain in the northeast until the security situation improves. The spokesman of the Minister, Colonel Tukur Gusau, said Dan-Ali gave the directive after meeting with the Service Chiefs on Monday at the Ship House, Headquarters of Ministry of Defence. Gusau said the minister also directed the General Officer Commanding of the 8 Division, Nigerian Army to relocate his Tactical Headquarters from Sokoto to Gusau, Zamfara state to oversee the conduct of Operation SHARAN DAJI. He added that the Chief of Defence Staff and Chief of Army Staff were also mandated to effect changes in the operational commands of Operations DELTA SAFE in the Niger Delta, LAFIYA DOLE in the North East, SHARAN DAJI in Zamfara and Katsina states and AWATSE in the South West. He said this is to enable them meet up with the current threats and security challenges in their areas of responsibility. He said the President and Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces has also directed the emergency procurement of critical equipment for the Armed Forces of Nigeria in line with the Federal Government policy of procuring equipment from Original Equipment Manufacturers through government to government basis. He said they also considered and approved the promotion of qualified senior military officers to their next higher ranks. He also said in a show of concern to the welfare needs of members of the Armed Forces, the President also directed the enhancement of the welfare of troops particularly those serving in operational areas within the country. Buhari meets security chiefs, departs for Bauchi Step up your game, Buhari tells security chiefs ‘Police, civil defence must patrol liberated areas in N/East’